(46, 450, 'Very nice idea for PNRI virtual tours! Nakakamiss na nga ang face-to-face tours dito tulad ng dati <3 ', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', 'Thank you for dropping by and appreciating our virtual tour! To learn more about our upcoming events and activities, you may visit our website www.pnri.dost.gov.ph and like us on Facebook https://fb.me/PNRIDOST ‚öõÔ∏è Keep exploring!', '2021-12-09 13:06:29'),
(47, 457, 'what‚Äôs the purpose of this?', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Hello! Thank you for your question.\nThe Atomic Research Center contains varying laboratories, equipment and instruments of PNRI that enables the research on the diverse applications of nuclear energy, such as nuclear instrumentation, health physics, isotope techniques, chemical research, applied physics and more.\n\nTo get to know more what we do at PNRI, you may visit the exhibits at https://aewph.com/lobby.\nYou may also visit our website: https://www.pnri.dost.gov.ph/.\n\nWe hope you enjoyed the virtual tour. Thank you! Keep exploring!', '2021-12-09 13:35:59'),
(48, 486, 'What is the importance of research? Do you think its useful for the future?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Greetings!\nYes, definitely. :)\nTo create new technologies, one must know how things work. To know how things work is to do research about it.\n\nThe Philippine Nuclear Research Institute have been conducting research in the diverse uses of nuclear energy that would propel our technology, which in turn, would help the varying sectors of our country, such as the agricultural, industrial, medical, environmental and many more.\n\nAs an example, PNRI has contributed to the agricultural sector by using nuclear energy to:\n1) Sanitize food through food irradiation\n2) Food Authenticity\n3) Disinfestation of pest from agricultural products\n4) Increase fertilizer efficiency\n5) Prolonging food shelf-life\nAnd much, much more.\n\nAll of these can only be achieved through research. :)\n\nIf you wish to know more, you may  check our exhibits at https://aewph.com/lobby . You may also like our facebook page (https://www.facebook.com/PNRIDOST) and check our website at https://www.pnri.dost.gov.ph/ .\n\nThank you! Keep exploring! ', '2021-12-09 15:17:56'),
(49, 489, 'This is nice.\n', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Thank you for dropping by and appreciating our virtual tour! To learn more about our upcoming events and activities, you may visit our website www.pnri.dost.gov.ph and like us on Facebook https://fb.me/PNRIDOST ‚öõÔ∏è Keep exploring!', '2021-12-09 15:36:52'),
