(68, 557, 'First, thank you for that new knowledge! According to the video, most hospitals here in our country, the Philippines, are still importing Tc99m from other countries. Is it possible that in the coming years/in the near future we are the ones to provide and produce Tc99m for hospitals for the whole country so that we don\'t have to import from other countries? Thank you!', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Yes, with the increase in the number of facilities producing radio pharmaceuticals and the workforce required to operate them, it is possible that in the future, we will no longer import Tc99m. ', '2021-12-09 21:08:18'),
(69, 557, 'First, thank you for the new knowledge! Paano po kung hindi na maaaring gamitin ang waste na inyong makukuha? Maraming salamat po!', 'Radiation Protection Services', NULL, '2021-12-09 21:34:24'),
(70, 557, 'First, thank you for the new knowledge! Limitado lang po ba ang mga lugar na maaaring lagyan ng SOMER? Thank you!', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-09 21:48:38'),
(71, 557, 'First, thank you for the knowledge! If I were given a chance to go and have a tour inside this facility/laboratory, would I be allowed to test a product/thing that I am curious to know more? Thank you!', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Of course! you may submit a sample of your material and have it tested. To learn about how to avail this service, please visit https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/', '2021-12-09 22:11:19'),
(72, 557, 'First, thank you for the new knowledge! Ligtas pa rin po bang i-consume o gamitin ang mga bagay after irradiation process? Thank you!', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Hello! Magandang araw! Salamat sa iyong katanungan. Kami\'y nagagalak dahil ikaw ay may natutunan sa aming Virtual Tour!\n\nPara sa iyong katanungan, Oo, ligtas pa din i-consume o gamitin ang mga bagay pagkatapos itong ma-subject sa irradiation. Sa katunayan, mas ginagawang safe gamitin o kainin ang  mga cosmetic products at food spices na ating ginagamit.  ', '2021-12-09 22:21:37'),
(73, 557, 'First, thank you for the new knowledge! Ano po yung pinakamalaking tulong ng PRR-1 para sa ating bansa? Maraming salamat po!', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hello! Maraming salamat po sa inyong tanong!\nMarami pong gamit ang isang research reactor tulad ng PRR-1, ngunit ang pinakamalaking maitutulong nito sa ating bansa ay ang \'capacity-building\': ang edukasyon at pagsasanay sa mga estudyante, mga professional, at mga scientist sa nuclear science and technology. ', '2021-12-09 22:35:13'),
(74, 561, 'What universities in our country get access to SATER or can use it?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hi! This would be open to everyone, especially to those taking nuclear education programs, training courses and experiments. :)', '2021-12-09 23:13:43'),
(75, 574, 'Maaari po bang maging \"too much\" ang process ng irradiation na magdudulot sa radioactive na food?', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Mabuhay! Salamat sa iyong katanungan. Ang irradiation ay hindi ginagawang \"Radioactive\" ang isang pagkain or produkto kapag ito\'y na expose sa radiation. \n\nBagama\'t na-iradiate ang mga pagkain, mas ginagawa nitong safe ang mga pagkain at pinapahaba ang \"shelf-life\" ng mga ito. Kaya\'t ang mga pagkaing na irradiate ay accepted bilang export quality products.', '2021-12-09 23:18:29'),
(76, 574, 'I really like the concept of this sculpture! How has this held up over the years? Did the past storms and earthquakes require you to reattach some parts?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', 'Thank you for your appreciation of the Humane Growth of Nuclear Sciences monument, which is artist Eduardo Castrillo\'s interpretation of the sub-atomic particles moving through space. It is made of brass and luckily has never needed any remodeling or special maintenance since its installation in 1977.', '2021-12-09 23:32:09'),
(77, 574, 'Paano po nakaapekto ang pandemya sa proseso at dami ng produkto sa irradiation?', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Mabuhay! Salamat sa iyong katanungan! Maraming bagay ang naapektuhan ng pandemyang kinaharap natin ngayon. Kahit kami sa PNRI ay lubos ding naapektuhan. Ang ating irradiation facilty sa ngayon ay nataon na pansamantlang tumigil sa operasyon dahil sa nakatakda nitong pag upgrade at expansion ng capcaity. Kaya ang upgrade ng irradiation facility ay nataon sa kasagsagan ng peak ng pandemya. ', '2021-12-09 23:40:51'),
(78, 574, 'Is the PNRI library open to the general public these days? Or is it temporarily closed due to the pandemic?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'Thanks for your interest in visiting the PNRI Library! Unfortunately, the institution is temporarily closed for visitors due to the pandemic. We look forward to seeing you face-to-face someday. In the meantime, you may visit https://bit.ly/pnrilibrary for remote library assistance. You can also like us on Facebook https://fb.me/PNRIDOST/ for updates regarding our upcoming virtual events and activities.', '2021-12-09 23:48:50'),
(79, 574, 'Awesome tour! Dati wala akong alam about this topic. But now, thanks to your virtual sessions, exhibits, and tours, I have learned more each day. Hope to visit!', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', 'Thank you for dropping by and appreciating our virtual tour! To learn more, head over to our education resource page: https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial.  For information on our upcoming events and activities, you may visit our website www.pnri.dost.gov.ph and like us on Facebook https://fb.me/PNRIDOST ‚öõÔ∏è Keep exploring!', '2021-12-09 23:53:25'),
(80, 561, 'How can I reach goals and achievements like him in the mere future?', 'General Medina Monument', 'That is a hard question to answer, but hard work, making sacrifices and perseverance is the key. Gen. Medina struggled in Mathematics as a child, but after spending an entire summer studying and working hard in Math, he went back to school performing much better in the subject. ', '2021-12-10 00:51:43'),
(81, 590, 'Is he still alive?', 'General Medina Monument', 'No, Brigadier General Florencio Medina already passed away.', '2021-12-10 06:46:21'),
(82, 590, 'How many his children is?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 06:49:36'),
(83, 581, 'How did he achieve this kind of career?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 08:36:18'),
(84, 581, 'Who can benefit from your training building?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'The PNRI is the only government agency mandated to promote nuclear science and technology int he country. This educational mandate is an essential part in PNRI\'s effort to engage the public in the discipline of nuclear science and technology, together with the maintenance of a vigorous research program and the building and operation of state-of-the-art research facilities. Scientists, researchers, professionals in the nuclear utilization field, faculty and students and all other interest groups of society can benefit from the research and training facilities of PNRI. ', '2021-12-10 08:38:09'),
(85, 581, 'Who can enter the PNRI facility?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 08:47:59'),
(86, 537, 'What could possibly happen if our suit has been contaminated with radioactive materials? ', 'Radiation Protection Services', NULL, '2021-12-10 08:50:52'),
(87, 581, 'How much the tc99m generator?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'To inquire about the cost, please contact the PNRI Isotope Technique Section by calling the Trunkline (+632) 929-6010 to 19 local 248. ', '2021-12-10 08:55:39'),
(88, 581, 'Do the sculpture have meanings?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', 'Yes, the Humane Growth of Nuclear Sciences monument is artist Eduardo Castrillo\'s interpretation of the sub-atomic particles moving through space. Its plaque reads: \"Reaching to the heights yet firmly rooted to the earth... epitomizes the commitment of the Filipino nuclear scientist to the task of utilizing the energy from the atom for the peaceful applications in agriculture, industry, medicine, and public health towards the realization of national goal as envisioned for the Filipino people...\"', '2021-12-10 08:56:52'),
(89, 598, 'Thank you for this virtual tour! It is very helpful po. By the way, what happens if it (SOMER) gets damaged? Does it get replaced po?  ', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 09:10:46'),
(90, 598, 'Is it open for visitation po? Are there requirements or some rules if we want to go there? Thanks :)', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Thank you for your interest in visiting PNRI. Unfortunately, the institution is closed for visitors at the moment due to the pandemic. We look forward to see you face to face someday. In the meantime, you may learn more about us through our website www.pnri.dost.gov.ph or explore more videos of our events and activities through our YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UChW6K3k2iSAc1Om_ivERaeQ.', '2021-12-10 09:19:03'),
(91, 598, 'Pili lang ba po yung food products na pwedeng sumailalim sa irradiation? Or pwede po sa lahat ng uri ng food products? Thanks po.', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Hello! Magandang umaga! Karamihan sa mga pagkain ay pwedeng ma-irradiate. Halimbawa na lamang ang mga mangga na ineexport natin sa ibang bansa ay pinapa-irradiate muna bago ito dalhin or ipadala sa ibang bansa, dahil dito ang ating manga ay pumpasa sa mga export quality conditions.\n\nIsa pang halimbawa ay ang mga packed food na pwede magamit sa mga disaster stricken areas. Tulad na lamang ng mga NutriBAr at packed adobo na after irradiation ay tumatagal ang shelf life ng mga nasabing pagakin na ito.\n\nMarami pang pagkain ang pwedeng isailalim sa irradiation, ngunit ito ay pinag aaralan muna bago ito magamit o makain.', '2021-12-10 09:27:31'),
(92, 599, 'Good morning/afternoon. I would like to ask, for how long did he commission in PAEC, which is now PNRI? And what was his most remarkable work? Thank you very much :) ', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 09:31:27'),
(93, 599, 'Good evening/day! I think this is a terrific place but from a member\'s perspective, I would like to ask, do you think this facility is a great environment for training? How so? What is special about this facility? Thank you very much.', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'The PNRI is the only government agency mandated to promote nuclear science and technology int he country. This educational mandate is an essential part in PNRI\'s effort to engage the public in the discipline of nuclear science and technology, together with the maintenance of a vigorous research program and the building and operation of state-of-the-art research facilities. Scientists, researchers, professionals in the nuclear utilization field, faculty and students and all other interest groups of society can benefit from the research and training facilities of PNRI. ', '2021-12-10 09:36:31'),
(94, 598, 'If we were to visit the facility, kailangan po bang magsuot ng protective equipment or equipments like facemasks and lab gowns?', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Hello! definitely once you entered a facility you need to wear personal protective equipment or PPE. So that you are safe during your visit to the facility.', '2021-12-10 09:39:25'),
(95, 598, 'Is there a meaning behind the sculpture po?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', 'The Humane Growth of Nuclear Sciences monument is artist Eduardo Castrillo\'s interpretation of the sub-atomic particles moving through space. Its plaque reads: \"Reaching to the heights yet firmly rooted to the earth... epitomizes the commitment of the Filipino nuclear scientist to the task of utilizing the energy from the atom for the peaceful applications in agriculture, industry, medicine, and public health towards the realization of national goal as envisioned for the Filipino people...\"', '2021-12-10 09:40:49'),
(96, 599, 'Greetings! Thank you very much for this knowledge! You explained in a great way. I would just like to know the advantages and disadvantages of reusing or functioning PRR 1 once again? Thank you very much!', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hello! That\'s a very good question.\nThe old PRR-1 facility has resources and structures that can still be used. So as not to waste the potential of these assets, these would be repurposed for the operation of the newer PRR-1 SATER Research Reactor. :)', '2021-12-10 09:43:36'),
(97, 608, 'What is special about Medina? ', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 09:44:00'),
(98, 614, 'Is your training facility is safe against COVID-19?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'While no system is 100% safe, we ensure that all minimum health standards (mask, physical distancing, face shield) for COVID-19 are followed. Additionally, about 97% of PNRI personnel are fully vaccinated!', '2021-12-10 09:54:33'),
(99, 614, 'Does every hospital in the Philippines have the tc99m?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'No. Not every hospital in the Philippines needs Tc99m. Additionally, only hospitals with a nuclear medicine facility are authorized to handle radio pharmaceuticals. Learn more about nuclear science and health by checking out our Nuclear 101 education resource materials - https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial', '2021-12-10 09:57:13'),
(100, 598, 'Is this accessible by anyone po? Like, is there an age requirement? Also, what are the common things that researchers do here? Thanks po.', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Hello! \n\nResearchers conduct laboratory experiments that involve nuclear and radiation applications. \n\nThey also offer services to the public such as elemental analysis, food authenticity, water resource analysis (isotope hydrology) and many more using nuclear techniques. Due to the pandemic, technical visits are still very limited and restricted.\n\nTo get to know more what we do at PNRI, you may visit the exhibits and virtual tour at https://aewph.com/lobby .\nYou may also like our facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/PNRIDOST or visit our website: https://www.pnri.dost.gov.ph/.', '2021-12-10 10:01:06'),
(101, 598, 'What are his contributions on the history of nuclear science/research?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:03:28'),
(102, 614, 'How many years did it take for the sculpture to be finished?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:04:40'),
(103, 617, 'ano ang mangyayari sa taong masyadong expose sa irradiation', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Mabuhay! Maraming salamat sa iyong katanugan, ang isang taong masyadong na expose sa radiation ay posibleng ma apektuhan ang kanyang kalusugan. Kaya dito sa PNRI sa tulong ng Radiation Protection Services Section masusuing binabantayan ang mga radiation workers mula sa epekto ng sobrang exposrue sa radiation.', '2021-12-10 10:09:21'),
(104, 614, 'Do you accept visit tours for groups of students who are interested in the field of research in the near future? ', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! Before the pandemic, we usually open PNRI to groups of students and visitors to tour inside our facilities. Thank you for your interest and we hope to see you in the future.', '2021-12-10 10:09:47'),
(105, 614, 'How frequently do you check the SOMER to gather data?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:12:45'),
(106, 620, 'Today, we are in a pandemic, a lot of buildings have closed due to regulations. Is the Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training (NART) still open for training courses and seminars?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'Due to the pandemic, all training courses and seminars being are being conducted online or through a blended approach.', '2021-12-10 10:15:57'),
(107, 614, 'What might happen if our suit becomes polluted with radioactive materials?', 'Radiation Protection Services', 'The soil, water ways, and environment might become contaminated depending on the type of radioactive waste if it is not stored properly. That is why if the radioactive source is not being used anymore, it is best to send it to the Radioactive Waste Management Facility for proper storage. The radioactive wastes are properly processed before being stored. They are enclosed in special capsule. These capsules are then stored in drums with very thick concrete lining inside to make sure the waste is properly kept in such a way that waste is and also so that it can be properly shielded. The Radioactive Waste Management Facility follows standards to secure the radioactive wastes stored in the bunkers.', '2021-12-10 10:16:34'),
(108, 619, 'How did General Medina Monument manage to become the father of atomic energy in the Philippines? ', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:16:41'),
(109, 610, 'Hello good morning! Where in the Philippines is this facility located? Does this have other branches here in the Philippines? Is there any effects in the foods/products that are exposed in irradiation? Thank you!', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Hello! As of the moment, we only have one electron beam facility located in the heart of Diliman, Quezon City, it is where the PNRI is situated. But there is a future commercial irradiation facility that will soon be built in Tanay, Rizal.\n\nRegarding the effects, there are no known incidents happened related to food irradiation, moreover, food irradiation makes our food much safer to eat and it also prolongs the shelf life.\n\nFor other products like polymeric materials, once subjected to irradiation, it will make the material more durable like rubbers in wire insulation and vehicle tires. \n\nFor agricultural products, we have this product called carrageenan foliar inorganic fertilizer in which helps boost rice, crops, and fruit-bearing trees to increase its yield.\n', '2021-12-10 10:24:03'),
(110, 622, 'Is the philippine government focused on making future servants of Science?if so how can we?', 'General Medina Monument', 'The advancement of science, technology and innovation is part of the Philippine Development Plan (https://pdp.neda.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/PDP-2017-2022-07-20-2017.pdf). To learn more about government support mechanisms in science and technology, head over to our education resource material site: https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial and check out the booklet on Careers in nuclear S&T. Happy reading!', '2021-12-10 10:24:08'),
(111, 619, 'What kind of training process is conducted at the Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training building?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'Trainings related to radiation safety, technology diffusion, reactor engineering, emergency preparedness and other nuclear science and technology related courses, seminars and workshops are being conducted at the NART building.', '2021-12-10 10:24:11'),
(112, 610, 'Where does Humane Growth of Nuclear Science is located? What is the specific height of this sculpture? Thank you!', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:28:45'),
(113, 620, 'WOW! The SOMER is very helpful and a great project! But I\'m wondering how did you come up with the SOMER concept? What inspired you? especially on the structure. Have you ever detected an alarming radiation in our country today?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:29:55'),
(114, 620, 'What perception or knowledge of Mr. Medina shared the PNRI that greatly impacted the Institute? That changed one scientist\'s perception in the field of science particularly nuclear science?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:34:59'),
(115, 618, 'If you\'re not interested in science or research, how can creativity and critical thinking certainly assist a student?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Creativity and critical thinking are life long learning skills applicable in all areas of life. The decisions you make affect the quality of your life. And if you want to ensure that you live your best, most successful and happy life, you\'re going to want to make conscious choices. That can be done with critical thinking and creativity! These skills are developed not only in science classes but also in non-science fields. Critical thinking certainly goes beyond just thinking clearly - it\'s also about thinking for yourself. : ))', '2021-12-10 10:36:40'),
(116, 618, 'If you\'re not interested in science or research, how can creativity and critical thinking certainly assist a student?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Creativity and critical thinking are life long learning skills applicable in all areas of life. The decisions you make affect the quality of your life. And if you want to ensure that you live your best, most successful and happy life, you\'re going to want to make conscious choices. That can be done with critical thinking and creativity! These skills are developed not only in science classes but also in non-science fields. Critical thinking certainly goes beyond just thinking clearly - it\'s also about thinking for yourself. : ))', '2021-12-10 10:37:56'),
(117, 620, 'How long did it take to build the sculpture? How does it symbolizes the human growth of nuclear science?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:38:46'),
(118, 610, 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER) is very nice and helpful equipment. Who invented this? Thank you!', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:40:04'),
(119, 625, 'What are the achievements that Bgen. General Medina have done in PNRI?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 10:43:07'),
(120, 620, 'What can you say po about the products especially food products that claims it\'s authenticity but actually false? What factors do you consider on the products that undergo and cannot undergo PNRI testing?', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Regulation standards for food authenticity are being crafted and enforced by the Food and Drug Administration. At the moment the use of nuclear analytical techniques for food authenticity is not yet part of the regulations. Hence, request for testing at PNRI is only done by manufacturers voluntarily.', '2021-12-10 10:52:36'),
(121, 619, 'When is the estimated possible release date of TC-99M in Philippine hospitals?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Tc-99m are released to hospitals as they are ordered. This has been the case since 2014 when the facility was given authorization to operate by the Food and Drug Administration. To learn more, head over to our education resource page - https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial.', '2021-12-10 10:56:38'),
(122, 617, 'what happen to the person who are too expose in irradiation', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', NULL, '2021-12-10 11:02:21'),
(123, 617, 'ano ang mangyayari sa taong masyadong expose sa irradiation', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Lahat ng sobra ay masama. Ang taong masyado expose sa radiation ay maaring magkaroon ng mga masamang epekto nito gaya ng \"radiation induced sickness\". Pero ano ang sukatan ng \"masyadong expose\"? Basahin at alamin ang Booklet ng \"Ionizing Radiation and Matter\" - https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial.', '2021-12-10 11:02:37'),
(124, 620, 'How many hospitals in the Philippines already avail the Tc99m generator? How will you encourage the rest of the hospitals and the citizens (in cities and provinces) to support this project and also use it, I know there are people who are still scared on the thought of \'nuclear\'.', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Education is key! People in general, fear what they do not understand.', '2021-12-10 11:03:04'),
(125, 628, 'Good morning! Thank you for the interactive game platform. Definitely a great way to spark interest. \nWhy did the PRR-1 shut down for more than 30 years?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hello!\nAfter operating for 2 decades, the PRR-1 was shutdown due to the aging of some of the components, equipment and structures. ', '2021-12-10 11:09:49'),
(126, 619, 'What kind of products goes through the process of gamma spectrometer, X-ray Flourescence Spectrometer, and LSC? Why?', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Different nuclear analytical techniques are used for different purposes. For instance, we can use X-ray fluorescence to find out the elements to which a sample is made of. Solid, gas and liquid samples can be tested in gamma spectrometers, x-ray fluorescence analyzers, etc. To learn more, head over to our education resource page - https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial.', '2021-12-10 11:09:50'),
(127, 620, 'What changes did you notice on the products that went the Irradiation process? How can you compare it to the product that didn\'t went under the Irradiation process?', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! Thanks for your question. Well, the effect of radiation depends on what kind of product you are subjecting to irradiation. But, generally, the interaction of radiation with matter depends on whether it will degrade, crosslink, polymerize, or graft. The end goal of irradiating products is to make them much better than their original qualities.\n\nOne example is the electronic components such as capacitors and resistors. After irradiation, these components have a larger capacity for electricity to pass through and are more electrical resistant than before, respectively.\n\nSome materials are functionalized for a certain purpose like our abaca fabric that can adsorb heavy metals in water.\n\nThere are many applications of radiation in our everyday life. And you can further explore it through our website at www.pnri.dost.gov.ph', '2021-12-10 11:12:29');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `visitor`, `question`, `about`, `answer`, `date_asked`) VALUES
(128, 630, 'What is the main goal for building this facility?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'The PNRI is the only government agency mandated to promote nuclear science and technology int he country. This educational mandate is an essential part in PNRI\'s effort to engage the public in the discipline of nuclear science and technology, together with the maintenance of a vigorous research program and the building and operation of state-of-the-art research facilities. Scientists, researchers, professionals in the nuclear utilization field, faculty and students and all other interest groups of society can benefit from the research and training facilities of PNRI.', '2021-12-10 11:18:38'),
(129, 619, 'What is the sculpture called? How does this brass sculpture represent the dynamic applications derived from the energy of the atom in agriculture, medicine, and industry?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', NULL, '2021-12-10 11:19:24'),
(130, 620, 'What can you say about the studies that uses chitosan to extend the shelf life of a product? How did irradiation help the medical field? ', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', NULL, '2021-12-10 11:22:49'),
(131, 633, 'why are teacher\'s important to students? ', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'Because without teachers, there\'s no one who will direct students to the paths of knowledge, good values, traditions, ways to resolve day-to-day challenges, and shape the future! It\'s a two-way street, however, as teachers can only impart these when the student is ready. In a way, teachers are like enzymes, nature\'s catalysts for change. Enzymes don\'t create change in and of themselves. Rather they lower the threshold activation energy required for a reaction to proceed. As you may have learned in school, enzymes do this without being consumed themselves. After catalyzing a change to the point where the system reaches equilibrium, having achieved an optimal state, enzymes figuratively step back and watch for new reactions to speed up. When the biological conditions are right, the enzyme is there. When the student is ready, the teacher appears. Or, rather, the teacher has been there all along, like an enzyme, helping move things along when things need moving along and staying out of the way the rest of the time. ', '2021-12-10 11:26:36'),
(132, 619, 'What are the major studies conducted at PNRI? Can these experiments produce products that can be used in our daily lives? If yes, how so?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 11:26:46'),
(133, 619, 'What are the major studies conducted at PNRI? Can these experiments produce products that can be used in our daily lives? If yes, how so?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 11:26:54'),
(134, 620, 'Are there branches already of PNRI Institute outside Manila? What do researchers do inside the Atomic Research Center?', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Hi!\nThe PNRI has no branch outside Manila. (Not yet anyway.) :)\nResearchers conduct laboratory experiments that involve nuclear and radiation applications. We also offer services to the public and industries such as elemental analysis, food authenticity, material analysis  and many more using nuclear techniques. To get to know more what we do at PNRI, you may visit the exhibits and virtual tour at https://aewph.com/lobby . You may also like our facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/PNRIDOST or visit our website: https://www.pnri.dost.gov.ph/.', '2021-12-10 11:28:28'),
(135, 617, 'ano ang mangyayari sa taong masyadong expose sa irradiation', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Lahat ng sobra ay masama. Ang taong masyado expose sa radiation ay maaring magkaroon ng mga masamang epekto nito gaya ng \"radiation induced sickness\". Pero ano ang sukatan ng \"masyadong expose\"? Basahin at alamin ang Booklet ng \"Ionizing Radiation and Matter\" - https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial.', '2021-12-10 11:33:20'),
(136, 619, 'Are visitors allowed to enter facilities such as this? What are the safety precautions needed to be followed?', 'Radiation Protection Services', NULL, '2021-12-10 11:37:33'),
(137, 620, 'When will the PRR-1 SATER Research Reactor be functioning again? How can PRR-1 SATER help researchers expand their knowledge about nuclear science?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hi!\nHaving a functional research reactor is very helpful in the study of nuclear sciences. Not only students, but also professionals, engineers, and scientists could conduct their experiments and simulations using a research reactor to observe nuclear reactions and behavior.\nThe target date for the operation of the PRR-1 SATER would be on July 2022. :)', '2021-12-10 11:38:01'),
(138, 628, 'Good morning! Are there any side effects with irradiated food? Are there any significant differences in their observable features?', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! With regards to its harmful effects, there are no recorded incidents related to food irradiation. Moreover, instead of side effects, foods that are irradiated are more resistant to spoilage or infestation of insects, etc. Examples of this technology are the export of our Mangoes to other countries and packed food that can be used for disaster resilience.', '2021-12-10 11:42:46'),
(139, 619, 'What does irradiation do to the products? What is the process? And how are the bacterias killed?', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! Thanks for checking in. Well, the effect of radiation depends on what kind of product you are subjecting to irradiation. But, generally, the interaction of radiation with matter depends on whether it will degrade, crosslink, polymerize, or graft. \n\nSo for the case of the bacteria, when they are exposed to a certain amount of radiation they are sterilized, or their DNAs are degraded causing their death.', '2021-12-10 11:44:47'),
(140, 619, 'Are visitors allowed to enter facilities such as this? What are the safety precautions that are needed to be followed?', 'Radiation Protection Services', 'The visitors that can be allowed to visit on selected parts of the Institute. For instance, before the pandemic, the AEW technical exhibits showcases some of the laboratories in the PNRI. In addition, some trainings in the PNRI includes facility tour. In places where there is a potential exposure, the trainees are required to wear the personal dosimeters lent to them to monitor their exposure during the duration of the training.', '2021-12-10 11:48:00'),
(141, 620, 'I love how they really priority everyone\'s safety from start up until the end. Also, the products/equipment really go through a lot of process to ensure that it is safe once a researcher is exposed to it. It was fun! Thank you!', 'Radiation Protection Services', 'We are glad you enjoyed the virtual tour! Learn more about us through our website www.pnri.dost.gov.ph or explore more videos of our events and activities through our youtube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UChW6K3k2iSAc1Om_ivERaeQ.', '2021-12-10 11:48:40'),
(142, 600, 'After a long time exposed to different weather conditions and since it\'s brass sculpture, is it possible that it will be damaged like completely? If so, what will you do to restore it, like will you hire a sculptor to make it again?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', NULL, '2021-12-10 12:26:30'),
(143, 600, 'What is the best legacy of Brigadier General Florencio Media in the field of science among all the things listed above?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 12:26:52'),
(144, 600, 'How can it address laboratory-related tasks?', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Hello!\nThe Atomic Research Center contains many laboratories, housing state-of-the-art equipment and instruments for different kinds of experiments. :)', '2021-12-10 12:27:11'),
(145, 574, 'Is the current amount of SOMER stations sufficient for detection in the whole Philippines? Do you plan to establish more stations in different locations?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 12:41:01'),
(146, 574, 'Do you plan to establish more SOMER stations in varying locations in the Philippines?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 12:41:49'),
(147, 574, 'Do you think po ba na better na sumailalim ang lahat ng food products sa market sa irradiation? ', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Mabuhay! Napakaganda ng iyong katanungan. Maraming benefits ang naitutulong ng food irradiation sa merkado. Bagaman, lahat ng pagkain ay pwedeng sumalilaim sa food irradiation, mas mabuti pa din na siyasatin kung ano ang mahalagang pakay ng pag irradiate ng pagkain.  ', '2021-12-10 12:46:48'),
(148, 619, 'What does irradiation do to the products? What is the process? And how are the bacterias killed?', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! Thanks for checking in. Well, the effect of radiation depends on what kind of product you are subjecting to irradiation. But, generally, the interaction of radiation with matter depends on whether it will degrade, crosslink, polymerize, or graft. So for the case of the bacteria, when they are exposed to a certain amount of radiation they are sterilized, or their DNAs are degraded causing their death.', '2021-12-10 12:48:49'),
(149, 574, 'Yung monument po ba ay nasa unahan rin ng PNRI in real life like dito sa tour?', 'General Medina Monument', 'Hi, ang ating virtual tour ay artistic interpretation lamang ng PNRI compound, samakatwid ang pagkakaposisyon ng mga pasilidad dito sa mapa ay naiiba sa aktuwal na posisyon nito.', '2021-12-10 12:50:49'),
(150, 574, 'Where do the products of this generated go? Are they ordered by and sent to hospitals?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Yes, Tc-99m are sent to hospitals needing them as they are ordered. To learn more, head over to our education resource material and look for the booklet on Nuclear Science and Health: https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial', '2021-12-10 13:00:39'),
(151, 619, 'What kind of products undergo irradiation? How can irradiation effect samples like plants?', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! There are a lot of products that can be subjected to irradiation. Examples are the rubber insulations used in our electrical wires and the tires that we use in our vehicles. The effect of radiation in the mentioned example is that it makes it more durable and last long. \n\nFor biological samples like plants. Irradiation can help alter its gene, which results in better species of the plant that are sometimes typhoon or drought resistant, also it can cause better flowering and an increase in fruit yield. ', '2021-12-10 13:02:14'),
(152, 574, 'Do you plan po ba na magtayo ng more SOMER stations sa iba\'t ibang lugar ng Pilipinas?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 13:02:58'),
(153, 574, 'Before the pandemic, did you conduct tours here po?', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Yes. :)', '2021-12-10 13:06:29'),
(154, 619, 'How can student researchers take part in the testings? Is there any possible way for other students to be a part of a research team? ', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Hello!\nStudents may do collaborations with our researchers as advisers/co-advisers. An institute (e.g. school) may also form a partnership with PNRI.\nIf you wish to know more, you may visit our website and contact us at https://www.pnri.dost.gov.ph .', '2021-12-10 13:07:03'),
(155, 619, 'What are the major studies conducted at PNRI? Can these experiments produce products that can be used in our daily lives? If yes, how so?', 'Radiation Protection Services', NULL, '2021-12-10 13:08:15'),
(156, 648, 'Does the NART building  have an age restriction? If so, how old must one be to be able to visit or join the training building?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'No, the NART building does not have any age restriction. However, the PNRI facilities are temporarily closed for visitors due to the pandemic. In the meantime, feel free to like us on Facebook https://fb.me/PNRIDOST/ to learn more about our services and our upcoming events and activities. ‚öõÔ∏è', '2021-12-10 13:18:47'),
(157, 650, 'Is it far from Manila to reach the monument?', 'General Medina Monument', 'The General Medina Monument is located in the PNRI compound along Commonwealth Avenue and Central Avenue in Quezon City, which is approximately only 13km away from Manila. ', '2021-12-10 13:28:43'),
(158, 617, 'ano ang mangyayari sa taong masyadong expose sa irradiation', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Lahat ng sobra ay masama. Ang taong masyado expose sa radiation ay maaring magkaroon ng mga masamang epekto nito gaya ng \"radiation induced sickness\". Pero ano ang sukatan ng \"masyadong expose\"? Basahin at alamin ang Booklet ng \"Ionizing Radiation and Matter\" - https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial.', '2021-12-10 13:38:20'),
(159, 648, 'Is the IRMS able to test both solid and liquid products?', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Yes, both solid and liquid samples can be tested in the IRMS. To learn more, head over to our education resource page - https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/nstep/ResourceMaterial.', '2021-12-10 13:41:47'),
(160, 647, 'Good afternoon po! What level of radiation is considered high?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', NULL, '2021-12-10 13:48:04'),
(161, 653, 'How does his established organizations and agencies connects and helps each other on contributing and providing enough energy for his fellowmen? Also, what causes the changes of names of PAEC and NSDB?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 13:58:34'),
(162, 648, 'Are there any past occurrences where pests were still present in the irradiated food products?', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! So far there is no past incident in PNRI where pests are still present in food products like our export quality mangoes after irradiation. So far all of them were able to be exported to other countries.', '2021-12-10 14:07:50'),
(163, 653, 'Is there any purpose for the two-door opening of every rooms?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Public buildings like hospitals and government agencies are serving more people than residential building. The flow of people (and equipment) coming and going at a particular time is very high. So, to avoid chaos at a particular point of the building, it is advisable to provide more than one door. ', '2021-12-10 14:11:55'),
(164, 654, 'What is the monument made of?\n', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 14:13:27'),
(165, 647, 'Good afternoon po! Is there a possibility that microorganisms would still be present in food products even though they underwent irradiation? ', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Hi! This is a very good question. Ideally, food that is irradiated should be microbe-free but it depends on how food is handled after the process of irradiation. ', '2021-12-10 14:15:57'),
(166, 661, 'What other achievements did he make if it wasn\'t mentioned in the momentum?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 14:16:35'),
(167, 654, 'How many students could be allowed inside at the same time?', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Hello! Thank you for your question.\nDue to the pandemic, visits to the PNRI facilities are still restricted. However, if you want to know more what we do at PNRI, you may visit the exhibits and virtual tour at https://aewph.com/lobby . You may also like our facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/PNRIDOST or visit our website: https://www.pnri.dost.gov.ph/.\n\nThank you!', '2021-12-10 14:17:05'),
(168, 654, 'Could there be activities for the students to familiarize or pique their interests within the facilities?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hello!\nIt can be arranged. :) \nHowever, due to the pandemic, visits to PNRI facilities are restricted.  For the mean time, I hope you and the students will enjoy this virtual tour. :)', '2021-12-10 14:22:41'),
(169, 605, 'Hello Po! If PRR-1 is re-operated, how will it help Filipinos and the Philippines? Thank You PO!', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hello!\nThe PRR-1 SATER will help in the education and training of students in nuclear science and technology. Professionals, such as engineers and scientists, would also be able to conduct their experiments and simulations on nuclear-related research without the need of going abroad. This would further the knowledge and skills of our professionals, and in turn, it would improve the technology of our nation.\n\nThank you! Keep exploring!', '2021-12-10 15:04:47'),
(170, 677, 'why do we need to use food irradiation', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Hello! thank you for your question. We need to use food irradiation to prolong its shelf life and to sterilize it from microbes and pests.', '2021-12-10 15:09:03'),
(171, 681, 'What kind of course did he have?', 'General Medina Monument', NULL, '2021-12-10 15:10:19'),
(172, 681, 'what year Nuclear Administration found?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', NULL, '2021-12-10 15:12:56'),
(173, 681, 'how many laboraties are there in PNRI', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', '10 and counting.. üòä', '2021-12-10 15:15:13'),
(174, 681, 'Gaano po kaimportante sa ating buhay ang Technetium-99M', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Tc-99m is used in tens of millions of medical imaging and diagnostic procedures annually, making it the most commonly used medical radioisotope in the world. How important is it to life?... We\'d say pretty much! üòä', '2021-12-10 15:17:30'),
(175, 681, 'wow', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Nice to know that you are amazed by our tour with Smarty! Just keep learning!', '2021-12-10 15:19:13'),
(176, 688, 'omg Thank you po!ü•∞ü•∞ hope that i visit PNRI soon hshshhs', 'Radiation Protection Services', 'Thank you for your interest in visiting PNRI. We are glad you enjoyed the virtual tour! We also look forward to see you face to face someday. In the meantime, you may learn more about us through our website www.pnri.dost.gov.ph or explore more videos of our events and activities through our youtube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UChW6K3k2iSAc1Om_ivERaeQ.', '2021-12-10 15:23:45'),
(177, 1, 'Why is Brigadier General Florencio A. Medina called the Father of Atomic Energy in the Philippines?', 'General Medina Monument', 'Gen. Florencio Medina\'s contributions are instrumental in establishing the Philippine Atomic Energy Commission (now PNRI), of which he also served as the first commissioner. Today, PNRI is the leading government agency for nuclear research and development in the Philippines.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(178, 1, 'Is Gen. Florencio Medina still alive?', 'General Medina Monument', 'No, Brigadier General Florencio Medina passed away in 1990 at the age of 85.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(179, 1, 'Is the monument real? If so, where is it located?', 'General Medina Monument', 'The General Medina Monument is an actual monument located within the PNRI compound along Commonwealth Avenue and Central Avenue in Quezon City.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(180, 1, 'How and when can we visit the SOMER?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', 'To request a guided facility tour during the 50th Atomic Energy Week (December 5-9, 2022), you may e-mail Mr. Michael Sia at mcsia@pnri.dost.gov.ph \r\n\r\nOur regular facility tour resumes in January 2023. You may book a tour for free through this link: https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/portal/nids/Appoint', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(181, 1, 'How many SOMER stations are installed in the Philippines and where are they located?', 'System for Online Monitoring of Environmental Radiation (SOMER)', 'SOMER has fourteen (14) stations located in various regions of the Philippines.  \r\n\r\nThe 14th station was installed in Morong, Bataan, just a few meters away from the Bataan Nuclear Power Plant. Other sites include the Philippine Nuclear Research Institute (PNRI), PAGASA Stations in Legazpi City, Albay and Jaro, Iloilo, and also cities and towns such as Sinait, Ilocus Sur, Puerto Princesa, Palawan, Lapu-lapu City, Cebu, Guiain, Eastern Samar, and El Salvador City, Misamis Oriental.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(182, 1, 'Do we have other nuclear training facilities in the Philippines aside from the Nuclear Training Center found in the NART Building?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'To date, the PNRI is the only government agency mandated to promote and regulate nuclear science and technology in the country.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(183, 1, 'Is the PNRI Library open to the general public?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'The PNRI Library is open to the general public by appointment.  \r\n\r\nYou may schedule a visit through this link: https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/portal/nids/Appoint', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(184, 1, 'What is the significance of having a training center in a nuclear research facility?', 'Nuclear Administration, Regulatory and Training Building', 'Together with the maintenance of a vigorous research program and the operation of state-of-the-art research facilities, the educational mandate is an essential part of PNRI\'s effort to engage the public in the discipline of nuclear science and technology. The Nuclear Training Center (NTC) conducts courses on the basic principle of radiation protection and the peaceful application of nuclear technologies. The NTC also maintains a radioisotope laboratory and NDT facilities for use by trainees who are generally medical practitioners, science educators, researchers, engineers, and technicians. To add to this, the NTC manages the Research/ Thesis Advisorship Program and the Internship/ On-the-Job Training Program for students who wish to undertake the laboratory research part of his/her thesis at the PNRI or students who would like to use nuclear techniques and experience working with PNRI researchers in the laboratory, respectively.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(185, 1, 'How old is this facility? Is this the first Tc-99m facility in the Philippines?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'PNRI\'s Tc-99m generator facility was the first in the Philippines. It started operating in 2014 following the Food and Drug Administration\'s approval of its license to operate.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(186, 1, 'How can we avail of the Tc-99m Generator? How much would it cost?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'To inquire about the availability and the pricing of the Tc-99m radio-pharmaceutical, you may contact the PNRI Isotope Technique Section by calling the trunkline (+632) 929-6010 to 19 local 248.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(187, 1, 'Are they also producing Tc-99m-labelled radiopharmaceuticals? If yes, what are those?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Yes, initially, two of the most commonly used Tc-99m radiopharmaceuticals can be produced by PNRI. These are (1) Tc99m - MDP (Methylene Diphosphonate), a bone imaging agent, and (2) Tc99m - DTPA (Diethylenetriamine Penta Acetate), a renal imaging agent.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(188, 1, 'Is it possible for the Philippines to produce its supply of Tc-99m in the coming years or the future instead of importing from other countries?', 'Technetium-99M Generator Facility', 'Yes, with the increase in the number of facilities producing radiopharmaceuticals and the workforce required to operate them, it is possible that in the future, we will no longer need to import Tc99m.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(189, 1, 'What does the sculpture symbolize?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', 'The Humane Growth of Nuclear Science monument is artist Eduardo Castrillo\'s interpretation of the sub-atomic particles moving through space. Its plaque reads: Reaching to the heights yet firmly rooted to the earth... epitomizes the commitment of the Filipino nuclear scientist to the task of utilizing the energy from the atom for the peaceful applications in agriculture, industry, medicine, and public health towards the realization of national goal as envisioned for the Filipino people...', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(190, 1, 'How do you clean an outdoor sculpture this massive?', 'Humane Growth of Nuclear Science', 'The Humane Growth of Nuclear Science sculpture can be considered as an art. Hence, any action that may directly affect the materials used in constructing the sculpture and any alterations in the sculpture are not encouraged. Furthermore, the sculpture is exposed to different weather conditions 24/7, thus, it is expected that there will be slight changes in its physical appearance as time passes. It is made of brass and luckily has never needed any remodeling or special maintenance since its installation in 1977.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(191, 1, 'What kinds of products go through the process of gamma spectrometer, x-ray fluorescence spectrometer, and LSC? Why?', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Nuclear analytical techniques are used for various purposes. For instance, we can use x-ray fluorescence to analyze the elements that make up a sample. Meanwhile, solid, gas, and liquid samples can be tested using gamma spectrometers, x-ray fluorescence analyzers, etc.  ', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(192, 1, 'Is XRF safe to use?', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Yes, XRF itself is designed with safety in mind. Additionally, users of XRF are required to undergo training before they are given the authorization to use the machine.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(193, 1, 'Does PNRI allow walk-ins to use the machines for testing?', 'Nuclear Analytical Techniques Applications Section', 'Currently, the PNRI does not allow walk-ins for such services. To schedule an appointment, check out: https://services.pnri.dost.gov.ph/portal/natas/welcome', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(194, 1, 'How can we make sure the products that have undergone irradiation are fully sterilized? Are there instances where there are radiation-resistant microbes found on the products?', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Products after irradiation are sent to a microbiological laboratory to check if products are already sterile. Regarding radiation-resistant microbes, it\'s on a case-to-case basis, and usually, products are studied first before they are subjected to irradiation.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(195, 1, 'Is there a possibility for the process of irradiation to be overdone and cause food to become radioactive? ', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'Irradiation does not make food or products radioactive upon radiation exposure. Aside from making the food safer to eat, irradiation allows food to have a longer shelf-life, therefore, is an excellent way to ensure products are export-quality.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(196, 1, 'What changes can you observe in the products which have undergone irradiation? How can they be compared to products which have not?', 'Cobalt-60 Multipurpose Irradiation Facility', 'The effect of radiation depends on what kind of product you are subjecting to irradiation. But, generally, the interaction of radiation with matter depends on whether it will degrade, crosslink, polymerize, or graft. The end goal of irradiating products is to make them much better than their original qualities. One example is electronic components such as capacitors and resistors. After irradiation, these components have a larger capacity for electricity to pass through and are more electrical resistant than before. Some materials are functionalized for certain purposes, like our abaca fabric that can adsorb heavy metals in water. There are many applications of radiation in our everyday life. And you can further explore it through our website at www.pnri.dost.gov.ph', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(197, 1, 'Pili lang ba ang food products na pwedeng sumailalim sa irradiation? Or pwede sa lahat ng uri ng food products?', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'Karamihan sa mga pagkain ay pwedeng ma-irradiate. Halimbawa na lamang ang mga mangga na ineexport natin sa ibang bansa ay pinapa-irradiate muna bago ito dalhin or ipadala sa ibang bansa, dahil dito ang ating manga ay pumpasa sa mga export quality conditions. Isa pang halimbawa ay ang mga packed food na pwede magamit sa mga disaster-stricken areas. Tulad na lamang ng mga NutriBAr at packed adobo na after irradiation ay tumatagal ang shelf-life ng mga nasabing pagakin na ito. Marami pang pagkain ang pwedeng isailalim sa irradiation, ngunit ito ay pinag aaralan muna bago ito magamit o makain.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(198, 1, 'Where in the Philippines is this facility located? Does this have other branches here in the Philippines? Are there any effects in the foods/products that are exposed to irradiation? Thank you!', 'Electron Beam Irradiation Facility', 'We only have one electron beam facility located in the heart of Diliman, Quezon City, it is where the PNRI is situated. But there is a future commercial irradiation facility that will soon be built in Tanay, Rizal. Regarding the effects, there are no known incidents related to food irradiation. Moreover, food irradiation makes our food much safer to eat and it also prolongs shelf life. For other products like polymeric materials, once subjected to irradiation, it will make the material more durable like rubbers in wire insulation and vehicle tires. For agricultural products, we have this product called carrageenan foliar inorganic fertilizer which helps boost rice, crops, and fruit-bearing trees to increase its yield.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(199, 1, 'What‚Äôs the purpose of this facility?', 'Atomic Research Center', 'The Atomic Research Center contains various laboratories, equipment and instruments of PNRI that enables the research on the diverse applications of nuclear energy, such as nuclear instrumentation, health physics, isotope techniques, chemical research, applied physics and more.  ', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(200, 1, 'How can student researchers take part in the testing? Is there any possible way for other students to be a part of a research team?', 'Atomic Research Center', 'Students may do collaborations with our researchers as advisers/co-advisers. For students who are interested in undertaking the laboratory research part of his/her thesis at the PNRI, they may contact the Nuclear Training Center by calling the trunkline (+632) 929-6010 to 19 local 236. ', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(201, 1, 'What are the advantages and disadvantages of reusing or functioning the PRR-1? ', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hello! That\'s a very good question. The old PRR-1 facility has resources and structures that can still be used. In order to not waste the potential of these assets, these were repurposed for the operation of the PRR-1 Sub-critical Assembly for Training, Education, and Research (SATER). ', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(202, 1, 'When will the PRR-1 SATER be functioning again? How can PRR-1 SATER help researchers expand their knowledge about nuclear science? ', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Having a functional research reactor is very helpful in the study of nuclear sciences. It will not only be for students, but also for professionals, such as engineers and scientists, who wish to conduct their experiments and simulations using a research reactor to observe nuclear reactions and behavior. The PRR-1 SATER was recently commissioned last June 2022. ', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(203, 1, 'How would the PRR-1 SATER help our country?', 'Philippine Research Reactor - 1', 'Hello! The PRR-1 SATER will help in the education and training of students in nuclear science and technology. Professionals, such as engineers and scientists, would also be able to conduct their experiments and simulations on nuclear-related research without the need to go abroad. This would further the knowledge and skills of our professionals, and in turn, it would improve the nuclear science and technology of our nation.', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(204, 1, 'What might happen if our suit becomes polluted with radioactive materials?', 'Radiation Protection Services', 'The soil, water ways, and environment might become contaminated depending on the type of radioactive waste if it is not stored properly. That is why if the radioactive source is not being used anymore, it is best to send it to the Radioactive Waste Management Facility for proper storage. The radioactive waste is properly processed before being stored. They are enclosed in a special capsule, which are then stored in drums with very thick concrete lining inside to make sure the waste is properly kept in such a way so that it can be properly shielded. The Radioactive Waste Management Facility follows standards to secure the radioactive waste stored in the bunkers. ', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
(205, 1, 'Are visitors allowed to enter facilities such as this? What are the safety precautions that need to be followed?', 'Radiation Protection Services', 'The visitors that can be allowed to visit selected parts of the Institute. For instance, the Atomic Energy Week technical exhibits showcase some of the laboratories in the PNRI. In addition, some local and international trainings conducted in PNRI include a facility tour. In places where there is potential exposure, the trainees are required to wear the personal dosimeters lent to them to monitor their exposure during the duration of the training. ', '2022-12-02 15:23:45'),
